node.text:
Follow @fightthroughmentalhealth for worldwide mental health support. 

#SUICIDEPREVENTIONMONTH.

Here are some ways to make someone who is suicidal feel loved:
• Listen to them, without judgement.
• Ask them if there is anything you can do to help.
• Be present.
• Remind them they are loved. 
💗💗💗💗💗

node.text:
Follow me @fightthroughmentalhealth for awareness & support all year round!

Here are some ways we can help to prevent suicide - 

💙 Accepting mental illnesses as real illnesses rather than dismissing them as just sadness. 
💜 Educate yourself about mental illness 
Be kinder to others online and in real life. 
💙 Stop making jokes about suicide. 
💜 Be present physically. You don’t have to fix someone, but letting them know you care is important. 
💙 Check in in loved ones instead of expecting them to reach out. 

#suicidepreventionmonth #depressionawareness #depressionhelp #depression #suicideprevention #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #mentalillness #anxietyawareness #anxiety

September is #SuicidePreventionMonth.
Please share this to raise awareness, as not many people are aware.

Everyone talks about suicide when it happens, but no one talks about the signs and the mental health issues that come before it.
This is why, as a society, we need to do more.

node.text:
This month is #SuicidePreventionMonth. Please share this as far and wide as you can to spread awareness. 

Follow @fightthroughmentalhealth for more awareness. 

Here are some suicide warning signs:
⚠️ social withdrawal
⚠️ a persistent drop in mood
⚠️ disinterest in maintaining personal hygiene or appearance
⚠️ uncharacteristically reckless behaviour
⚠️ poor diet changes
⚠️ rapid weight changes
⚠️ being distracted
⚠️ anger
⚠️ insomnia
⚠️ alcohol or drug abuse
⚠️ giving away sentimental or expensive possessions

#mentalhealthawareness #mentalillnessmatters #mentalhealth #mentalillness #suicideprevention 
#mentalhealthsupport #depression #anxiety #mentalhealthrecovery #mentalhealthadvocate
